Checked src/PIL/Image.py just now — I don't see any 'backup' string in the file, so your change may not have landed yet (or got overwritten). Current state of the block (lines ~2567-2598) is:

        created = False
        if dry_run:
            fp = io.BytesIO()
        elif open_fp:
            created = not os.path.exists(filename)
            if params.get("append", False):
                # Open also for reading ("+"), because TIFF save_all
                # writer needs to go back and edit the written data.
                fp = builtins.open(filename, "r+b")
            else:
                fp = builtins.open(filename, "w+b")
        else:
            fp = cast(IO[bytes], fp)

        try:
            save_handler(self, fp, filename)
        except Exception:
            if open_fp and not dry_run:
                fp.close()
            if created:
                try:
                    os.remove(filename)
                except PermissionError:
                    pass
            raise
        finally:
            try:
                del self.encoderinfo
            except AttributeError:
                pass
        if open_fp and not dry_run:
            fp.close()

Please add your backup logic inside the 'elif open_fp:' branch, after 'created = not os.path.exists(filename)', so it only runs on the real write path (not dry_run). Sorry for any overlap — go ahead and re-apply on top of this.
